						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar set up in the graveyard (now removed to the bund of the tank) in the village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara Pandiḍlapalli Kannāradēvarāju: Śaka 1195, Śrīmukha.</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to record a gift of land to the temple of Sēturāmēśvara. One of the faces of this pillar appears to be dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1[6]86 Chitrabhānu</hi> and mentions GuḍipāTi Subbarāju NArāyaṇappaṁgāru.<note n="438-1">See Appendix for text.</note></p>						

						</summary>
